==English==

===Etymology===
* From {{OE.}} [[secan|sēċan]], with influence from Old Norse [[sœkja]], whence the hard /k/ sound (compare [[beseech]]).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/si:k/}}
* sēk
* {{audio|en-us-seek.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: '''Homophones''': [[Sikh]]
*: [[Rhymes:English:-iːk|Rhymes: -iːk]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|seeks|seeking|sought}}

# To [[try]] to [[find]], to look for.
#: ''I '''seek''' wisdom.''

